                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 367.11/16.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador to Great
                            Britain</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-11-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 9, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Under Secretary in Chargé of Near Eastern affairs says that the British
                    Embassy was instructed November 6 to extend protection in their discretion to
                    Americans; he took note of your request of November 8 that commanders of British
                    vessels in Turkish waters receive similar instructions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reid.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
